Few hours after Burna Boy’s aide blasted the singer’s ex-girlfriend, bestie of Stefflon, Empress, has risen in her defence. Empress said contrary to the accusation, her friend did not produce a track to diss the grammy award winner. She said that Stefflon had recorded those songs while the duo were still lovers. She also said the Grammy award singer will never find a woman as good as his recent ex-girlfriend.   Actress Mercy Aigbe gives husband head cut     I want a private wedding – Temi Otedola     Aide kicks as Burna Boy’s ex releases song   “She hasn’t even dropped the song yet. What’s all this disrespectful chat that’s never wronged Burna ever. “For your information, no song she ever dropped was for Burna. She actually recorded most of them while still with him “Please, don’t let me speak because Steff begged me not to. Steff is the best woman this man will ever see in his life “Tell your friends to have some respect None of you should speak abeg,” she stated.